{"id":"nc-rom-editor-1kt","title":"Implement ROM modification tracking and project management","description":"Create a Git-like modification tracking system for ROM edits with project organization.\n\n## Problem Statement\nUsers currently track ROM modifications manually in Excel spreadsheets. Multiple ROMs often have the same filename (e.g., 'stock.bin'), making organization difficult. Need a built-in system to:\n- Track all table modifications with comments\n- Organize multiple ROMs under projects with aliases\n- View change history and compare versions\n- Export modification logs\n\n## Core Features\n\n### 1. Project Management System\n**Purpose:** Organize related ROMs under a single project\n- Create/open/save projects (.ncproj files)\n- Project contains: name, description, list of ROMs\n- Each ROM has an alias (user-friendly name like 'Stock', 'Stage 1', 'Final Tune')\n- Projects stored as SQLite database or JSON file\n- Recent projects list in File menu\n\n### 2. Modification Tracking\n**Purpose:** Record every table edit automatically\n- Track when table values are changed\n- Record: timestamp, table name, address, old value, new value, user comment\n- Store baseline (original ROM) for comparison\n- Automatic tracking (no manual saving required)\n- Optional: attach comments when making changes\n\n### 3. Change History Viewer\n**Purpose:** View all modifications made to a ROM\n- List all changes chronologically\n- Filter by: table name, date range, comment text\n- Show before/after values\n- Edit/add comments retroactively\n- Undo changes (revert to previous value)\n\n### 4. Comparison Tools\n**Purpose:** Compare ROMs and track differences\n- Compare current ROM to baseline (show what changed)\n- Compare two ROMs in the same project (Stock vs Tuned)\n- Highlight modified tables in tree view\n- Show delta values (e.g., '+5.0', '-10%')\n- Visual diff viewer for tables\n\n### 5. Export \u0026 Documentation\n**Purpose:** Generate modification reports\n- Export change log to PDF/text/CSV\n- Include: all changes, comments, timestamps\n- Useful for documentation or sharing with tuner\n\n## Technical Design\n\n### Data Model\n\n\n### Storage Options\n1. **SQLite Database** (recommended)\n   - Single .ncproj file\n   - Efficient querying for history/filtering\n   - Supports large projects\n   \n2. **JSON File** (simpler alternative)\n   - Human-readable\n   - Easier to implement\n   - May be slow for large change logs\n\n### Implementation Phases\n\n**Phase 1: Project Structure (Foundation)**\n- Create Project data model\n- Implement project file format (SQLite schema or JSON structure)\n- Add File \u003e New Project, Open Project, Save Project\n- Add ROM to project with alias\n- Basic project settings dialog\n\n**Phase 2: Change Tracking Backend**\n- Modify table_viewer to emit change events\n- Create ChangeTracker class to record modifications\n- Store baseline ROM data when project is created\n- Intercept write_table_data() calls to log changes\n- Add comment dialog when saving changes\n\n**Phase 3: Change History UI**\n- Create ChangeHistoryWindow to display modifications\n- List all changes with filters (date, table, comment)\n- Show old value → new value\n- Allow editing comments\n- Add Tools \u003e Change History menu\n\n**Phase 4: Comparison Features**\n- Compare current ROM to baseline (modified tables indicator)\n- Compare two ROMs side-by-side\n- Add visual indicators in table browser (modified tables)\n- Highlight changed cells in table viewer\n- Delta calculation and display\n\n**Phase 5: Export \u0026 Polish**\n- Export change log to PDF/text/CSV\n- Add project templates\n- Project backup/restore\n- Settings: auto-comment frequency, track anonymous changes\n\n## UI Mockups\n\n### Main Window Changes\n- Menu: File \u003e New Project, Open Project, Recent Projects\n- Menu: Tools \u003e Change History, Compare ROMs\n- Status bar: Show current project name\n- Table browser: Icon/color for modified tables\n\n### Change History Window\n\n\n### Comment Dialog (when saving changes)\n\n\n## Example Use Case\n\n**Scenario:** User is tuning their NC Miata\n\n1. Create project: 'NC1 Stage 1 Tune'\n2. Add ROMs:\n   - 'Stock' (baseline)\n   - 'Working Tune' (current edits)\n3. Edit fuel table in 'Working Tune'\n4. App prompts: 'Add comment?' → 'Richened WOT for safety'\n5. Later: View change history → see all modifications with comments\n6. Compare 'Working Tune' to 'Stock' → see all differences\n7. Export change log → PDF report for dyno shop\n\n## Dependencies\n- Requires table editing functionality (nc-rom-editor-3in.6)\n- Nice-to-have: ROM comparison tool (nc-rom-editor-3in.8)\n\n## Benefits\n- No more Excel spreadsheets\n- Complete audit trail of changes\n- Professional documentation\n- Easy comparison of tune versions\n- Safer tuning (can revert changes)\n- Share change logs with tuners/shops","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-06T20:18:35.042153846-05:00","created_by":"root","updated_at":"2026-01-06T20:18:35.042153846-05:00","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"nc-rom-editor-1kt","depends_on_id":"nc-rom-editor-3in","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-06T20:18:47.146121306-05:00","created_by":"root"}]}
